public static int processGetValue(java.lang.String iRequest,
                                  boolean iDefDelimiters,
                                  SCODataManager ioSCOData,
                                  DMProcessingInfo oInfo)
Processes a GetValue() against a known set of SCO run-time data (SCODataManager.

Parameters:
iRequest - A dot-notation binding of the desired data model element.
iDefDelimiters - Indicates if the value returned should include default delimiters.
ioSCOData - An instance of the SCODataManager that contains the run-time data for the individual SCO.
oInfo - Provides the value of this data model element. Note: The caller of this function must provide an initialized (new) DMProcessingInfo to hold the return value.
Returns:
An abstract data model error code indicating the result of this operation.
